{[#]I had entered this ending with great expectations and rightly so. Do you
find a win for White?} 34. h3 $2 {This spoils the win.} ({I spent nine of my
remaining 20 minutes on calculating the consequences of} 34. g4 $1 {but failed
to come to the right conclusion.} fxg4 (34... g6 {simply allows White keeping
a reserved tempo with respect to the game:} 35. gxf5 gxf5 36. h3 h5 37. h4 b6
38. Kc3 Kc5 39. Kb3 Kd5 40. Kb4 Kc6 41. b3 $18) 35. Kxe4 $1 ({For a few
minutes I thought} 35. f5 {would be winning but then noticed the saving plan:}
h5 36. Kxe4 h4 37. Kf4 g3 38. hxg3 hxg3 39. Kxg3 Ke5 40. Kg4 Ke4 $11) 35... g6
(35... Ke6 36. f5+ Kf6 37. Kf4 h5 38. e4 g5+ 39. fxg6 Kxg6 40. e5 $18) (35...
h5 36. Kf5 g6+ 37. Kg5 Kd5 38. f5 gxf5 39. Kxf5 $18) 36. f5 g5 37. f6 Ke6 38.
f7 Ke7 $5 (38... Kxf7 39. Kf5 {transposes below.}) 39. Ke5 $1 ({Only this wins.
During the game, I failed to notice that the position arising after} 39. Kf5
Kxf7 {is a mutual Zugzwang. Here it is White to move and he cannot win:} 40. e4
Kg7 41. e5 Kf7 42. b3 b4 43. axb4 b5 44. e6+ Ke7 45. Kg6 Kxe6 46. Kxh6 Kf6 $11)
39... Kxf7 40. Kf5 Kg7 41. e4 ({I stopped my calculating after} 41. Kxg4 Kg6 {
with at least equality for Black.}) 41... Kf7 42. e5 Ke7 43. Kg6 Ke6 44. Kxh6
Kxe5 45. Kxg5 $18) 34... h5 35. h4 g6 36. Kc3 Kc5 37. Kb3 Kc6 (37... b4 38.
axb4+ Kd5 $11 {is also good.}) 38. Kb4 Kb6 {In the similar line above Black
did not have this square for the king.} 39. Kc3 Kc5 40. Kb3 Kc6 41. Kb4 Kb6 42.
b3 Kc6 43. Kc3 Kc5 44. Kc2 b6 45. Kd2 b4 46. a4 Kd5 1/2-1/2

