{[#]Instead of the natural 22...Nb3, with chances to equalize, Black decided
forcing matters with} 22... Qb7+ $6 23. Nd5 Rfd8 {Your answer?} 24. Qe7 $1 ({
Indeed, this is the best way to simplify to a favorable endgame. If} 24. bxc5
$6 Rxd5 25. Qe4 Rad8 {Black should draw without any special problems.}) 24...
Nd7 (24... Qxe7 {more or less loses a pawn.} 25. Nxe7+ Kf8 26. Nc6 Nb3 (26...
Rxd1 27. Rxd1 Ne4 28. Nxe5 $16) (26... Rdc8 27. Nxe5 $16) 27. Nxd8 (27. Rxd8+
Rxd8 28. Rb1 Nd2 29. Rd1 Rc8 30. Nxe5 Rc2 31. f3 f6 32. Nd7+ Ke7 33. Nc5 $16)
27... Nxa1 28. Nxf7 Kxf7 29. Rxa1 Rc8 30. Rd1 Ke6 31. Kf3 $16) 25. Rac1 Re8 (
25... Rac8 $2 26. Rc7 Rxc7 27. Qxd8+ Kh7 28. Qxc7 $18) 26. Qxd7 $5 ({I thought
this to be the most practical, even though I did not find any problem in the
lines with} 26. Qd6 Rad8 (26... Re6 27. Qc7 Qa7 28. Qxa7 Rxa7 29. Rc7 Rxc7 30.
Nxc7 Re7 31. Nxa6 $16) 27. Rc7 Qa8 28. Rxd7 Rxd7 29. Qxd7 Rd8 30. Qf5 Rxd5 31.
Qe4 Rd8 32. Rxd8+ Qxd8 33. Qxe5 $16 {With excellent winning chances in the
queen ending.}) 26... Qxd7 27. Nf6+ gxf6 28. Rxd7 a5 (28... Re6 29. Rcc7 Rf8
30. g4 {followed by the King's advance is also hopeless.}) 29. Rcc7 axb4 30.
axb4 Rec8 $6 (30... Rf8 31. Rb7 Ra2 32. e3 Rb2 33. Rd6 $1 (33. Rxb5 Rc8 34. Rd6
Kg7 35. Rbb6 f5 36. Rf6 Rxb4 37. Rxh6 Rxb6 38. Rxb6 f6 $14) 33... Kg7 34. Rbb6
f5 (34... Rxb4 35. Rxf6) 35. Rxb5 $16 Rc8 36. Rxe5 Rcc2 37. Rxf5) 31. Rb7 Rab8
32. Rxf7 Rxb7 33. Rxb7 Rc2 34. e3 Rb2 35. Rxb5 Kf7 36. Rb8 f5 37. b5 e4 38. b6
Kg7 39. b7 Rb1 40. Kh3 (40. f4 $5 $18) 40... Rb3 41. Kh4 Rb4 42. g4 1-0

