{[#]White has some queenside pressure but Black thought of neutralizing it
completely with} 20... Nd5 $5 {Were his hopes justified? ***Not really!} 21. e4
$3 {This simplifies by force to a very promising ending, based on Black's
hanging d7-knight and White's rooks' centralization..} Nxc7 (21... Rxc7 22.
exd5 Rxc1 23. Rxc1 exd5 24. Rc7 $18) 22. Nc6 Bg5 23. f4 $1 Nb8 $8 24. fxg5 Nxc6
25. Rxc6 $16 {With the usual endgame pressure, to which the kingside space
advantage surely adds.} Ne8 26. Rdc1 Rxc6 27. Rxc6 Kf8 28. Kf3 Ke7 29. Nc5 a5
30. Rb6 Nd6 (30... b4 31. e5) (30... Nc7 31. e5 $1 b4 32. Ke4 $1 $16) 31. Nb7
$1 Nc4 (31... Rb8 32. Nxd6 Rxb6 33. Nc8+ Kd7 34. Nxb6+ Kc6 35. Nc8 Kc7 36. Na7
$18 {Suba.}) 32. Rxb5 $18 Rb8 33. a4 Kd7 34. b3 Ne5+ 35. Rxe5 Rxb7 36. Rxa5
Rxb3+ 37. Kf4 Rb2 38. h4 Rf2+ 39. Ke3 Rf1 40. Ra7+ Ke8 41. a5 h6 $6 (41... g6
42. a6 Ra1 43. g4 $1 Kf8 44. h5 {/\h6}) 42. g6 $1 $18 fxg6 43. Rxg7 Ra1 44.
Rxg6 Kf7 45. Rxh6 Rxa5 46. Kf4 Ra6 47. g4 Kg7 48. g5 1-0

