$2 14. dxc5 Rxc5 15. Qxd8 Bxd8 16. Bb4 $18) 14. Bxf3 $1 (14. Nxf3 Nc4 15. Bc3
c5 $132) 14... c5 15. Rad1 cxd4 16. Bb7 Rb8 17. Bxa6 $14) 13... c5 (13... Bxf3
{can be answered wifferently than in the similar line above as b2 is defended.}
14. Nxf3 Nc4 15. Be1 c5 16. b3 Na3 17. Qb2 b4 18. dxc5 Rxc5 19. Ne5 $16) 14.
Qd3 $146 c4 (14... cxd4 15. Rxc8 Bxc8 16. Nxd4 $16 {offers White strong
