will remain with an extra pawn. White should be fast.} 1. Nxf7 $1 {Quite a
typical sacrifice in such positions. Now, Black's king will be out of his
comfort zone for a long time.} Kxf7 2. dxe6+ Kxe6 3. Qf3 {White has an
overwhelming initiative for the piece. Black is behind in the development and
it is not clear how his king will get out of the center.} *

