{The move 7...b6 is not as strong against 7.Qa4 as it is against 7.Qc2. Can
you show why?} 1. Ne5 $1 {The most principled continuation. We should prevent
Black's light-squared bishop from occupying the long diagonal.} Qxd4 2. Bxa8
Qxe5 3. Nc3 $1 {A developing move taking advantage of the fact that the queen
attacks both on a7 and c4. With the queen on c2 this would make less sense.} *

