Nevertheless, the pin along the a5-d8 diagonal is annoying. How can White make
use of it?} 1. Qd3 $1 {White is ready to enter a symmetric position since his
pieces are better coordinated. It is important to know that the move} c4 {
is well met by} 2. Qb1 {The tension is released and now White has an upperhand
in the center. His next move is e2-e4. Later on, he can make use of his space
to develop a kingside initiative.} *

