{Black has just played 13...h6 forcing White to clarify the position of his
bishop. What should White proceed?} 1. Bxf6 {This is a thematic exchange in
Catalan positions. Now, White can carry out the central e2-e4 adavance.} Qxf6
2. e4 $1 Qd8 {Black's idea is obvious. He is planning to prepare the c7-c5
advance by means of Nbd7.} 3. Nbd2 Nd7 4. Nb3 $1 {White managed to occupy the
center and to prevent his opponent from playing c7-c5.} *

