{Black has just played 14...b4, preventing Nc3 and creating the plan ...Na5
followed by ...c7-c5, when Black could use the knight for retrieving the pawn
with ...Nb7. How should White arrange his pieces?} 1. Qf1 $1 {Very strong
positional move. White prepares Be1 followed by Nbd2. The following logical
line is likely to arise.} Bd5 2. Be1 Rc8 3. Nbd2 Na5 4. Ne5 $1 {Immediately
making use of the fact that Black's knight does not control the center anymore.
} c5 5. dxc5 Bxc5 6. Nd3 Bf8 7. Bxd5 Nxd5 8. e4 {Black has managed exchanging
pawns, but White's better coordination leave him with lasting initiative.} *

